Product Backlog

Goals:
Our goal is to create a secure, student-only marketplace that reduces the financial burden of attending college. In the long term, we aim to make books and electronic devices more accessible and affordable for students.

Functions/ Features:
1. User Account Registration
Students can create accounts using their school email and ID.

2. User Authentication and Login
Secure login and logout functions.

3. Student Verification
Verified college emails only can access the platform

4. User Profile Management
Users can view and edit profile information.

5. Item Listing Creation
Students can create and manage listings with a title, description, price, and category.

6. Image Upload for Listings
Users can upload images of their listings.

7. Item Listing Management
Users can modify or remove their own listings.

8. Marketplace Browsing
Users can browse all available listings.

9. Search Function
Users can search for listings.

10. 

User Stories:

As a student, I want to create an account using my school email so only verified students can access the marketplace.

As a student, I want to log in securely so my account and listings are protected.

As a student, I want to log out so others cannot access my account on shared devices.

As a seller, I want to post items for sale so other students can see them.

As a seller, I want to upload images to my listings so buyers can see the items.

As a seller, I want to edit my listings so I can update item details.

As a seller, I want to delete my listings so I can remove items that are no longer available.

As a buyer, I want to browse all available listings so I can find items easily.

As a buyer, I want to search listings by keyword so I can quickly locate specific items.

As a buyer, I want to filter listings by category so results are more relevant.

As a buyer, I want to filter listings by price range so I can stay within my budget.

As a buyer, I want to message sellers so I can ask questions before purchasing.

As a seller, I want to respond to buyer messages so we can coordinate the exchange.

As a user, I want to report unsafe or inappropriate listings so the platform remains safe.

As an admin, I want to review reported listings so I can remove content that violates rules.

